00:25:34,525 --> 00:25:37,859
Oh, I'm supposed to meet the site manager here.

268
00:25:39,592 --> 00:25:41,240
Stay right there.

269
00:25:41,240 --> 00:25:44,192
You could get hurt barging in here like that.

270
00:25:44,192 --> 00:25:45,725
Yes.

271
00:25:46,492 --> 00:25:48,592
Yes, Manager, where are you?

272
00:25:48,592 --> 00:25:50,725
There's someone here to see you.

273
00:26:05,159 --> 00:26:09,659
Don't worry too much about safety, that's what I'm saying.

274
00:26:09,659 --> 00:26:11,292
Yes.

275
00:26:12,659 --> 00:26:15,200
Look at that, there.

276
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:18,400
Hey, Ji Kang Hee, slipping away?

277
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:20,090
Why is this still here?

278
00:26:20,090 --> 00:26:22,450
Haven't you moved it to the second floor?

279
00:26:22,900 --> 00:26:25,700
This is why women are a problem.

280
00:26:25,700 --> 00:26:29,800
Who cares if she knows things or has a degree?

281
00:26:29,800 --> 00:26:31,400
Look at this. This!

282
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:34,100
You're as skinny as a stick.

283
00:26:34,100 --> 00:26:37,200
How would you do anything with this weak arm?

284
00:26:37,200 --> 00:26:39,290
Right?

285
00:26:42,092 --> 00:26:45,092
Hey, what are you doing?

286
00:26:45,100 --> 00:26:46,400
Let go, will you?

287
00:26:46,400 --> 00:26:48,125
I'm strong, you know?

288
00:26:48,125 --> 00:26:50,059
Ah, go away.

289
00:26:54,825 --> 00:26:56,692
Hey! You!

290
00:26:56,692 --> 00:26:58,359
Get out!

291
00:26:59,692 --> 00:27:01,492
I was going to quit anyway.

292
00:27:01,492 --> 00:27:04,559
I said I would quit if you messed with me one more time.

293
00:27:04,559 --> 00:27:05,859
Hey! Ji Kang Hee!

294
00:27:05,859 --> 00:27:09,092
Don't you dare show up at my site again!

295
00:27:14,600 --> 00:27:17,800
How rude, that disrespectful!

296
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,325
Oh my, that…

297
00:27:32,859 --> 00:27:34,492
Excuse me.

298
00:27:37,759 --> 00:27:40,125
I have something to ask.

299
00:27:41,659 --> 00:27:43,559
It's your first time at the site, right?

300
00:27:43,559 --> 00:27:45,659
Oh, yes.

301
00:27:47,500 --> 00:27:50,600
If you wear wide pants like this at the site,

302
00:27:50,600 --> 00:27:51,700
you can easily trip and fall.

303
00:27:51,700 --> 00:27:55,259
- Oh, I see. 
 - Put these ankle straps on.

304
00:27:58,200 --> 00:28:00,560
And wear a neck warmer if possible.

305
00:28:00,560 --> 00:28:02,400
It gets pretty dusty.

306
00:28:02,400 --> 00:28:06,000
Have you filled out the contract?

307
00:28:06,000 --> 00:28:07,900
No, not yet.

308
00:28:07,900 --> 00:28:11,200
- When you write the contract, you must make sure to check the daily payment date. 
 - Yes.

309
00:28:11,200 --> 00:28:14,300
As for the site, because the scaffolding is made of old recycled materials,

310
00:28:14,300 --> 00:28:16,700
- be extra careful when moving around. 
 - Yes.

311
00:28:16,700 --> 00:28:19,700
You don't have to worry about the foreman nagging to collect scrap metal,

312
00:28:19,700 --> 00:28:22,659
since he's just going to sell it and pocket the money anyway.

313
00:28:24,825 --> 00:28:27,525
I heard you used to be an interior designer.

314
00:28:28,325 --> 00:28:30,692
I heard it from the site manager.

315
00:28:30,692 --> 00:28:32,759
I'll introduce myself properly.

316
00:28:33,659 --> 00:28:37,692
My name is Hwang Jeong Goo, and I'm the new site supervisor.

317
00:28:39,725 --> 00:28:41,892
   

318
00:28:44,859 --> 00:28:47,825
How about starting over as a designer?

319
00:28:48,700 --> 00:28:51,300
Thanks for the offer, but I'm fine.

320
00:28:51,300 --> 00:28:53,800
Why? Because of the blacklist?

321
00:28:53,800 --> 00:28:55,600
Your pay was six months behind.

322
00:28:55,600 --> 00:28:58,600
Isn't it natural to report unpaid wages in such a situation?

323
00:28:58,600 --> 00:29:02,500
Know this, blacklisting and whatnot, it's a wrong practice to give disadvantages.

324
00:29:02,500 --> 00:29:05,000
Instead of working for dirty people like that, come to Moment and…

325
00:29:05,000 --> 00:29:07,600
Is Moment any different?

326
00:29:07,600 --> 00:29:10,200
Do you think I haven't tried?

327
00:29:10,200 --> 00:29:14,292
They say no educational restrictions, but won't accept a resume from a lower university.

328
00:29:15,992 --> 00:29:18,725
Please don't give me false hope.

329
00:29:22,125 --> 00:29:27,859
Then, instead of Moment, trust me, Hwang Jeong Goo, and come.

330
00:29:29,259 --> 00:29:33,459
I'll support and fight for you if anyone mistreats you this time.

331
00:29:34,525 --> 00:29:38,092
When can you prepare your portfolio?

332
00:29:57,800 --> 00:29:59,200
I've come to see the director.

333
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:01,000
What's your name?

334
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:03,459
It's Ji Kang Hee.

335
00:30:05,325 --> 00:30:07,525
- Just leave it here. 
 - Excuse me?

336
00:30:07,525 --> 00:30:10,525
The director is not here right now, so just leave it.

337
00:30:11,325 --> 00:30:12,325
I'll wait.

338
00:30:12,325 --> 00:30:14,225
Well, then... suit yourself.

339
00:30:26,600 --> 00:30:30,000
Unbelievable! She really came.

340
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,250
You know, the girl I talked about last time.

341
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:33,900
Director Hwang must be crazy.

342
00:30:33,900 --> 00:30:37,500
She should know better after being sent to a construction site instead of being appointed CEO.

343
00:30:37,500 --> 00:30:40,800
That's what I'm saying. She doesn't know how long she'll last.

344
00:30:40,800 --> 00:30:44,200
How could she bring in a nobody that was part of a construction crew?

345
00:30:44,200 --> 00:30:46,400
Obviously, the design team wouldn't take her.

346
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:49,000
Even I got demoted for being part of Director Hwang's team.

347
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:52,100
Would you take her? Someone who was doing manual labor…

348
00:30:52,100 --> 00:30:53,792
Excuse me.

349
00:30:54,592 --> 00:30:56,592
Ah, just a moment.

350
00:30:56,592 --> 00:30:58,792
Which school did you graduate from?

351
00:30:59,759 --> 00:31:01,859
Want to grab a coffee later?

352
00:31:01,859 --> 00:31:03,425
Okay.

353
00:31:35,180 --> 00:31:38,690
♫  Close your eyes and feel me here  ♫

354
00:31:38,692 --> 00:31:41,480
What? Why are you staring?

355
00:31:41,480 --> 00:31:45,225
♫  What color is in your mind?  ♫

356
00:31:45,225 --> 00:31:47,490
I know, that I'm not cool.

357
00:31:47,490 --> 00:31:53,225
♫  Blue, dark gray, calm and sweet  ♫

358
00:31:53,225 --> 00:31:55,200
I'm going back.

359
00:31:55,200 --> 00:31:59,300
I'm going to go back. I'm Ji Kang Hee!

360
00:31:59,300 --> 00:32:06,000
♫  Please tell me if you're standing here for me  ♫

361
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:12,400
♫   Far across the dream, just call my name  ♫

362
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:16,900
♫  Who's standing over the river  ♫

363
00:32:16,900 --> 00:32:20,200
♫  Here I am  ♫

364
00:32:20,200 --> 00:32:22,100
 Kang Hee, shall we have some ice cream? 

365
00:32:22,100 --> 00:32:24,159
 No. 

366
00:32:25,100 --> 00:32:27,300
 I heard a Berry Scoop opened in Central City. 

367
00:32:27,300 --> 00:32:29,500
 There are so many unique flavors. 

368
00:32:29,500 --> 00:32:31,925
 I'll buy it for you, okay? 

369
00:32:32,559 --> 00:32:34,490
 Look, this is a butterfly. 

370
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:37,450
 It only goes to pretty flowers. 

371
00:32:37,459 --> 00:32:40,425
 Huh? It's going towards you. 

372
00:32:43,492 --> 00:32:44,959
 Do you want to try it? 

373
00:32:48,925 --> 00:32:51,425
 Oh! It's here. We need to get on this one. 

374
00:32:52,125 --> 00:32:55,525
 Hello. For two, please. 

375
00:32:59,925 --> 00:33:01,892
 How did you know? 

376
00:33:01,892 --> 00:33:03,425
 Know what? 

377
00:33:04,425 --> 00:33:07,492
 How did you know the police came to the motel? 

378
00:33:07,492 --> 00:33:09,292
 I didn't know. 

379
00:33:12,192 --> 00:33:13,825
 Well. 

380
00:33:14,592 --> 00:33:18,959
 Affairs one moment and love triangle fights the next. 

381
00:33:18,959 --> 00:33:21,459
 Just when things calm down, a wanted fugitive shows up. 

382
00:33:21,459 --> 00:33:24,125
 There's always an investigation going on. 

383
00:33:25,800 --> 00:33:28,900
 But seriously, how did you know? 

384
00:33:28,900 --> 00:33:33,059
 How do you always know when to ask me to get ice cream with you? 

385
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:37,600
 I just know. I'm always looking at you. 

386
00:33:43,359 --> 00:33:45,092
 Don't look at me. 

387
00:33:45,800 --> 00:33:47,100
 Don't look at me, look forward. 

388
00:33:47,100 --> 00:33:50,400
 I said don't look, don't move. 

389
00:33:50,400 --> 00:33:53,000
 Just try to move. I'll kill you. 

390
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:59,800
♫  Please tell me, are you standing here, for us?  ♫

391
00:33:59,800 --> 00:34:06,100
♫  Far across the dream, just call my name?  ♫

392
00:34:06,100 --> 00:34:10,700
    
 ♫  Who's standing over the river  ♫

393
00:34:10,700 --> 00:34:17,000
♫  Here I am  ♫

394
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:21,080
♫  Where I am  ♫

395
00:34:39,200 --> 00:34:41,500
No wonder you got kicked off the design team.

396
00:34:41,500 --> 00:34:44,400
Director Hwang is a legend in this field of work, isn't she?

397
00:34:44,400 --> 00:34:48,500
When someone like her brings in a nobody from a construction site,

398
00:34:48,500 --> 00:34:50,900
shouldn't you be curious about their portfolio?

399
00:34:50,900 --> 00:34:52,800
- If you consider yourself a designer,  at the very least. 
 -  What do you think you're doing?

400
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:54,100
Aren't you curious?

401
00:34:54,100 --> 00:34:57,200
About what kind of designer I am, how skilled I am?

402
00:34:57,200 --> 00:35:00,500
I'll show you. Who I am and what kind of designer I am.

403
00:35:00,500 --> 00:35:02,400
- Sure, but not right no— 
 - You're not Director Hwang.

404
00:35:02,400 --> 00:35:04,000
Let me speak with her directly.

405
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:06,059
- Director went out… 
 - Move.

406
00:35:12,359 --> 00:35:14,092
You're here.

407
00:35:15,400 --> 00:35:18,300
Sorry, I couldn't hear anything from the outside.

408
00:35:18,300 --> 00:35:19,580
Your eye makeup looks great.

409
00:35:19,580 --> 00:35:21,400
The smoky shadow suits you so well.

410
00:35:21,400 --> 00:35:23,000
Do you always do it that way?

411
00:35:23,000 --> 00:35:25,659
Sometimes, only when necessary.

412
00:35:27,959 --> 00:35:30,625
It's like combat gear to me.

413
00:35:32,025 --> 00:35:34,200
I really like that attitude.

414
00:35:34,200 --> 00:35:35,900
Then what about weapons?

415
00:35:35,900 --> 00:35:37,100
Pardon?

416
00:35:37,100 --> 00:35:38,500
Weapons.

417
00:35:38,500 --> 00:35:40,125
Pardon?

418
00:35:46,759 --> 00:35:48,325
Your portfolio.

419
00:35:48,325 --> 00:35:50,092
Ah, yes.

420
00:35:58,025 --> 00:35:59,659
Shall we take a look?

421
00:36:30,300 --> 00:36:34,100
- Did you really do this yourself? 
 - Yes.

422
00:36:34,100 --> 00:36:35,400
That doesn't make sense.

423
00:36:35,400 --> 00:36:38,200
There'd be more than enough part-time jobs available

424
00:36:38,200 --> 00:36:40,740
if you're this good with CAD and SketchUp.

425
00:36:40,740 --> 00:36:42,200
I'm sure they'd pay better as well.

426
00:36:42,200 --> 00:36:44,700
It was the site of a blueprint I worked on.

427
00:36:44,700 --> 00:36:49,000
I wanted to see how a blueprint is turned into reality.

428
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:51,600
You're a step too late. Here's the CEO's pick.

429
00:36:51,600 --> 00:36:55,100
Graduated from Parsons in New York and completed an internship with the Rockwell Group.

430
00:36:55,100 --> 00:36:59,292
Not comparable to someone who graduated from a random college and worked at a construction site.

431
00:37:04,225 --> 00:37:06,092
Ms. Ji Kang Hee.

432
00:37:09,400 --> 00:37:11,500
The Grand Village in Hannam-dong.

433
00:37:11,500 --> 00:37:14,100
A 400-square-meter villa with a garden.

434
00:37:14,100 --> 00:37:16,000
It needs remodeling. What do you think?

435
00:37:16,000 --> 00:37:20,500
- It's a personal request I received, so there are no bidding nor budget limits. 
 - So what?

436
00:37:20,500 --> 00:37:23,100
I think you should do it, Mr. Mok.

437
00:37:23,100 --> 00:37:25,600
And Ms. Ji Kang Hee could learn a lot, too.

438
00:37:25,600 --> 00:37:27,500
But I'd need your approval, right?

439
00:37:27,500 --> 00:37:28,700
No, no.

440
00:37:28,700 --> 00:37:31,500
- It's your project, why should I? 
 - Then the credit would go to...

441
00:37:31,500 --> 00:37:33,900
You, of course.

442
00:37:33,900 --> 00:37:39,200
Just take Ms. Ji Kang Hee as the project designer.

443
00:37:39,200 --> 00:37:42,500
Let's start you out as an intern.

444
00:37:42,500 --> 00:37:45,200
We'll consider formal employment after working on the project together.

445
00:37:45,200 --> 00:37:47,100
And decide after three months.

446
00:37:47,100 --> 00:37:48,725
Deal.

447
00:38:00,425 --> 00:38:01,925
Um…

448
00:38:03,500 --> 00:38:05,200
Do you like me?

449
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:06,400
Pardon?

450
00:38:06,400 --> 00:38:09,600
Why go to such lengths, for someone you just met?

451
00:38:09,600 --> 00:38:13,100
Isn't this the second time? And we'll keep seeing each other going forward.

452
00:38:13,100 --> 00:38:15,900
You were the first to be kind to me when we met.

453
00:38:15,900 --> 00:38:18,100
I did that because I thought you were someone who came to work.

454
00:38:18,100 --> 00:38:20,100
Thanks to what you told me, I came to know

455
00:38:20,100 --> 00:38:23,600
about reinforcing bars being diverted, materials being fudged, and payments being delayed.

456
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:25,800
I was able to grasp the situation at once

457
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:29,292
and completely took control of the manager and his men.

458
00:38:30,092 --> 00:38:33,559
So I'm just repaying my debt.

459
00:38:38,625 --> 00:38:41,125
Thank you for the opportunity.

460
00:38:43,292 --> 00:38:46,025
Let's make one more thing clear.

461
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:51,459
I really like men.

462
00:39:43,159 --> 00:39:47,559
Hey, don't you ever get tired? Coming to Seoul every time you have a day off?

463
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:50,200
It's Seoul.

464
00:39:50,200 --> 00:39:51,600
Seoul, what about it?

465
00:39:51,600 --> 00:39:55,300
You know best what Seoul means to me.

466
00:39:55,300 --> 00:40:00,100
You really think you can coincidentally run into her?

467
00:40:00,100 --> 00:40:03,800
Wake up! Seoul's population is ten million. Ten million!

468
00:40:03,800 --> 00:40:05,900
Still, the possibility isn't zero.

469
00:40:05,900 --> 00:40:11,500
Then, on the off chance, you actually run into Ji Kang Hee.

470
00:40:11,500 --> 00:40:13,300
What would you do?

471
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:15,359
If we meet?

472
00:40:17,259 --> 00:40:19,825
Will I be able to recognize her?

473
00:40:21,525 --> 00:40:23,259
Ji Kang Hee.

474
00:40:32,300 --> 00:40:34,300
 Today is the client meeting. 

475
00:40:34,300 --> 00:40:39,100
 As I mentioned yesterday, please make sure you use your best discretion 

476
00:40:39,100 --> 00:40:41,700
 and select the best five drafts. 

477
00:40:41,700 --> 00:40:43,300
 - Yes. 
 - Yes, I understand. 

478
00:40:43,300 --> 00:40:44,400
- So Min. 
 - Yes?

479
00:40:44,400 --> 00:40:47,700
How much should we estimate for each draft?

480
00:40:47,700 --> 00:40:52,059
We are budgeting about 8,000 to 9,000 for each draft…

481
00:40:52,900 --> 00:40:55,600
8,000 to 9,000…

482
00:40:55,600 --> 00:40:56,900
Ms. Ji Kang Hee,

483
00:40:56,900 --> 00:41:01,700
an intern's job is to do as they're told and answer the phone. Go on.

484
00:41:01,700 --> 00:41:03,400
How long have you been sitting there?

485
00:41:03,400 --> 00:41:04,800
- That's what I'm saying... 
 - Um…

486
00:41:04,800 --> 00:41:07,400
Please increase the price per square meter a bit more.

487
00:41:07,400 --> 00:41:09,225
Ms. Ji Kang Hee.

488
00:41:10,725 --> 00:41:12,500
Why would an intern need business cards?

489
00:41:12,500 --> 00:41:15,100
Having a business card is the least you can prepare when meeting clients.

490
00:41:15,100 --> 00:41:16,400
You want me to take the intern?

491
00:41:16,400 --> 00:41:18,600
Of course, it's her responsibility.

492
00:41:18,600 --> 00:41:21,800
I've already let the clients know.

493
00:41:21,800 --> 00:41:23,892
Have a good meeting.

494
00:41:32,792 --> 00:41:35,159
Our intern is quite capable, isn't she?

495
00:41:35,159 --> 00:41:37,125
That's right.

496
00:41:39,159 --> 00:41:41,459
Thank you as always, Han Woo.

497
00:41:42,392 --> 00:41:44,292
What are you thanking me for again?

498
00:41:44,292 --> 00:41:47,092
Are there no difficult customers these days?

499
00:41:47,092 --> 00:41:48,930
Oh, why wouldn't there be?

500
00:41:48,930 --> 00:41:51,420
Don't even mention it… There was a big fuss yesterday.

501
00:41:52,259 --> 00:41:53,859
Oh, dear.

502
00:41:53,859 --> 00:41:56,259
I can't handle it anymore, either.

503
00:41:57,400 --> 00:42:01,400
- Would you like something to drink? It's on me. 
 - Really?

504
00:42:01,400 --> 00:42:04,200
In that case, why don't we recharge with some caffeine.

505
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:07,000
I was just feeling like I needed that.

506
00:42:07,000 --> 00:42:09,125
Sounds good.

507
00:42:10,225 --> 00:42:13,092
No, no, it has to be the most expensive one…

508
00:42:13,092 --> 00:42:16,359
No need for alternatives, second-best, cost-effectiveness, or anything of the sort.

509
00:42:17,525 --> 00:42:19,825
Just give me the best of whatever.

510
00:42:19,825 --> 00:42:22,859
Understood, I'll do my best.

511
00:42:24,592 --> 00:42:26,759
Pack up, it's time to go.

512
00:42:27,625 --> 00:42:30,192
Already? We haven't had our meeting yet.

513
00:42:32,759 --> 00:42:34,925
We just had the meeting.

514
00:42:36,400 --> 00:42:40,000
We need to meet the newlyweds who will actually live here, not just the person paying,

515
00:42:40,000 --> 00:42:41,900
to learn what kind of house they want.

516
00:42:41,900 --> 00:42:44,800
- What kind of interior do they want… 
 - It's our job to suggest that.

517
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:46,600
Start by preparing the concept board.

518
00:42:46,600 --> 00:42:50,592
We can't force people into a home; we need to make the proper house for them.

519
00:42:51,592 --> 00:42:54,892
I'm sorry, she is still an intern…

520
00:42:57,292 --> 00:42:58,759
Ms. Ji Kang Hee?

521
00:42:58,759 --> 00:43:00,059
Yes.

522
00:43:02,059 --> 00:43:03,725
That's a great point.

523
00:43:03,725 --> 00:43:05,859
I was shortsighted in my desire for a surprise.

