547
00:44:59,525 --> 00:45:01,192
It's on the company's card.

548
00:45:01,192 --> 00:45:02,992
Thank you.

549
00:45:18,225 --> 00:45:19,825
What's wrong?

550
00:45:19,825 --> 00:45:22,259
- Kang Hee… 
 - Huh?

551
00:45:23,092 --> 00:45:25,525
- Ji Kang Hee. 
 - Ji Kang Hee?

552
00:45:25,525 --> 00:45:27,192
- You saw her? 
 - Yeah.

553
00:45:27,192 --> 00:45:28,925
Hey, where?

554
00:45:28,925 --> 00:45:30,859
Where? Where?

555
00:45:30,859 --> 00:45:33,759
Where? Hey, you need to find her quickly!

556
00:45:33,759 --> 00:45:35,392
Hey, am I going alone?

557
00:45:35,392 --> 00:45:37,525
Come out!

558
00:46:00,025 --> 00:46:02,192
Are you sure you saw her?

559
00:46:08,059 --> 00:46:09,959
It was my grandfather.

560
00:46:09,959 --> 00:46:11,792
No, I'm telling you it was my mother.

561
00:46:11,792 --> 00:46:13,192
That's not true.

562
00:46:13,192 --> 00:46:17,192
Our parents agreed to wait until we graduated from college,

563
00:46:17,192 --> 00:46:18,959
but Grandfather rushed our marriage.

564
00:46:18,959 --> 00:46:22,025
So what? That's in the past.

565
00:46:22,025 --> 00:46:25,659
It's a fact that you ran away because you didn't like me.

566
00:46:25,659 --> 00:46:28,192
And I became the one lucky man.

567
00:46:28,192 --> 00:46:32,125
- Thank you, Seok Kyeong. 
 - Yes, thank you, Geum Seok Kyeong.

568
00:46:32,759 --> 00:46:35,592
Look at you, baby! You're so gorgeous.

569
00:46:35,592 --> 00:46:37,225
Don't do it.

570
00:46:37,225 --> 00:46:41,259
- No, I can't stop it. 
 - Don't do it, I said don't.

571
00:46:41,259 --> 00:46:44,092
Hey, stop it!

572
00:46:44,092 --> 00:46:45,659
I'm sorry.

573
00:46:47,725 --> 00:46:49,792
Shall we start the consultation?

574
00:46:49,792 --> 00:46:54,659
The problem is my tastes are too diverse.

575
00:46:54,659 --> 00:47:00,225
I like a wide range of things, so I'm not sure how to explain what...

576
00:47:00,225 --> 00:47:03,825
Just keywords or a mood that comes to mind?

577
00:47:03,825 --> 00:47:05,759
Feel free to share them comfortably.

578
00:47:05,759 --> 00:47:07,859
Keywords…

579
00:47:09,025 --> 00:47:10,525
Fun.

580
00:47:10,525 --> 00:47:11,792
Fun…

581
00:47:11,792 --> 00:47:15,692
I'd like our home to be cheerful and fun.

582
00:47:15,692 --> 00:47:18,425
I grew up in a strict and rigid environment.

583
00:47:18,425 --> 00:47:22,792
What do you think would be fun to do in this space?

584
00:47:23,959 --> 00:47:26,825
To be honest, when I was young,

585
00:47:26,825 --> 00:47:30,292
I wanted to have my own comic room

586
00:47:30,292 --> 00:47:32,492
to read comic books whenever I want to,

587
00:47:32,492 --> 00:47:35,659
and to invite friends over to play games.

588
00:47:35,659 --> 00:47:37,692
Like a rebel's hideout…

589
00:47:37,692 --> 00:47:40,859
Imagine if this room was a duplex.

590
00:47:41,659 --> 00:47:43,259
A duplex?

591
00:47:43,259 --> 00:47:45,125
Can this place be turned into a duplex?

592
00:47:45,125 --> 00:47:48,259
If we open up the slab of this room and raise the ceiling height, it's possible.

593
00:47:48,259 --> 00:47:51,525
You make it a duplex and separate the spaces.

594
00:47:51,525 --> 00:47:55,059
On the upper level, you could put a few bean bags

595
00:47:55,059 --> 00:48:00,225
and create a space entirely for yourself where you can read comics or books.

596
00:48:00,225 --> 00:48:03,725
And on the lower level, you could play games with friends

597
00:48:03,725 --> 00:48:07,592
and separate the areas so you could drink wine or coffee.

598
00:48:07,592 --> 00:48:09,125
That's so...

599
00:48:10,225 --> 00:48:12,125
perfect!

600
00:48:12,125 --> 00:48:14,325
There's a term called "man cave".

601
00:48:14,325 --> 00:48:17,859
Originally, it was a space for men's hobbies and such.

602
00:48:17,859 --> 00:48:21,425
But this space wouldn't be a "man cave"

603
00:48:21,425 --> 00:48:23,725
it would be an "Esther cave".

604
00:48:23,725 --> 00:48:26,292
Esther cave…

605
00:48:28,059 --> 00:48:32,692
Wow, was interior consulting always this fun?

606
00:48:32,692 --> 00:48:34,859
- Geum Seok Kyeong. 
 - Yes?

607
00:48:34,859 --> 00:48:38,725
Your gift is really cool. I really like it.

608
00:48:39,959 --> 00:48:41,825
Even more than mine, babe?

609
00:48:41,825 --> 00:48:44,992
Is our Victor so cute?

610
00:48:44,992 --> 00:48:46,025
Isn't he?

611
00:48:46,025 --> 00:48:47,492
Yes.

