613
00:49:05,925 --> 00:49:07,625
   

614
00:49:07,625 --> 00:49:09,125
   

615
00:49:16,459 --> 00:49:17,892
Let's call it a day.

616
00:49:17,892 --> 00:49:20,659
Why is she pulling an all-nighter when even we aren't?

617
00:49:20,659 --> 00:49:22,159
She's just a three-month intern.

618
00:49:22,159 --> 00:49:24,192
Does she think doing all that will buy her Mr. Mok's attention?

619
00:49:24,192 --> 00:49:26,692
In her dreams.

620
00:50:07,092 --> 00:50:08,425
Ms. Ji Kang Hee.

621
00:50:08,425 --> 00:50:09,359
Yes?

622
00:50:09,359 --> 00:50:12,492
I get that you're creative and diligent,

623
00:50:12,492 --> 00:50:16,392
but this design doesn't quite fit with our company.

624
00:50:18,425 --> 00:50:22,959
Is it me that doesn't fit or is it my design?

625
00:50:24,659 --> 00:50:28,359
I'll be honest with you. I am a person with prejudices.

626
00:50:29,092 --> 00:50:32,925
I think one's educational background, family, experiences, and appearance, are better.

627
00:50:32,925 --> 00:50:35,525
But I have no prejudices regarding ability.

628
00:50:35,525 --> 00:50:40,059
Can someone with prejudices really evaluate ability without bias?

629
00:50:40,059 --> 00:50:43,525
Isn't true ability about overcoming such prejudices?

630
00:50:43,525 --> 00:50:46,225
- The client may like my proposal.
 - This crap?

631
00:50:46,225 --> 00:50:48,825
I've reflected on what the client wants as much as possible

632
00:50:48,825 --> 00:50:50,625
and I've analyzed their lifestyle thoroughly.

633
00:50:50,625 --> 00:50:54,825
Ms. Ji Kang Hee, what do you know about the client?

634
00:50:54,825 --> 00:50:58,759
A friend gifts a 400-square-meter newlywed house as a wedding gift,

635
00:50:58,759 --> 00:51:00,725
regardless of the cost.

636
00:51:00,725 --> 00:51:02,425
It's another class.

637
00:51:02,425 --> 00:51:05,359
Someone at the bottom of life, living in a goshiwon and doing manual labor,

638
00:51:05,359 --> 00:51:08,359
couldn't possibly approach that world.

639
00:51:09,159 --> 00:51:11,525
Let's not wear each other out and just stop here.

640
00:51:11,525 --> 00:51:12,859
- Mr. Kim Daniel. 
 - Yes.

641
00:51:12,859 --> 00:51:16,025
- About that modern design earlier… 
 - Am I being fired right now?

642
00:51:16,025 --> 00:51:17,759
I acknowledge your CAD skills.

643
00:51:17,759 --> 00:51:20,725
I'll contact you if there's any part-time work.

644
00:51:20,725 --> 00:51:22,059
Bring the proposal here.

645
00:51:22,059 --> 00:51:23,492
Yes.

646
00:51:28,725 --> 00:51:30,159
Okay.

647
00:51:30,159 --> 00:51:32,559
- I think this is quite good. 
 - Oh, yes.

648
00:51:32,559 --> 00:51:34,992
It seems to have turned out really well in a woodsy style.

649
00:51:41,025 --> 00:51:42,659
- It's good. 
 - What?

650
00:51:42,659 --> 00:51:47,192
It's unique and cozy, yet chic.

651
00:51:47,192 --> 00:51:49,025
Chic?

652
00:51:49,025 --> 00:51:50,959
The color combination is no joke.

653
00:51:50,959 --> 00:51:54,825
If the furniture is refurbished in this style, it would look like a Mendini piece.

654
00:51:54,825 --> 00:51:56,959
You met Ji Kang Hee, right?

655
00:51:56,959 --> 00:52:00,159
Did you rush off to tattle that she was fired?

656
00:52:00,159 --> 00:52:01,860
You fired her?

657
00:52:01,860 --> 00:52:05,050
The head designer, during the project?

658
00:52:11,092 --> 00:52:13,259
What a shame.

659
00:52:13,259 --> 00:52:14,425
 Bull... 

660
00:52:14,425 --> 00:52:16,759
If there's a company looking for a designer, I'll reach out to you.

661
00:52:16,759 --> 00:52:19,392
 No thanks. Just stop talking about me behind my back. 

662
00:52:19,392 --> 00:52:20,692
You'll come to visit sometimes, right?

663
00:52:20,692 --> 00:52:22,392
 Would you come if you were me? 

664
00:52:22,392 --> 00:52:25,292
Shouldn't we at least have a farewell party?

665
00:52:25,292 --> 00:52:27,525
You'd do that, for me?

666
00:52:28,892 --> 00:52:30,325
Then, please do it.

667
00:52:30,325 --> 00:52:33,392
All right, let's set a date.

668
00:52:33,392 --> 00:52:35,059
It's been a pleasure.

669
00:52:35,059 --> 00:52:37,859
I'll go and greet the manager before I leave.

670
00:52:37,859 --> 00:52:40,259
I'm not asking you to use Ms. Kang Hee's design.

671
00:52:40,259 --> 00:52:42,600
I'm just asking to include it in the presentation with the other proposals,

672
00:52:42,600 --> 00:52:44,150
how is that overstepping?

673
00:52:44,159 --> 00:52:47,192
Do you think you're still the head of the design department?

674
00:52:47,192 --> 00:52:50,525
You were demoted because you lost your touch.

675
00:52:50,525 --> 00:52:52,392
Mr. Mok.

